\pard\f0\fs28\qc {\b 5.           Soldanella}            L.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs24\qc By S. Pawlowska.
\par 

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs. Leaves in a basal rosette,entire, coriaceous, evergreen, long-petiolate. Inflorescence scapose. Flowers nodding. Corolla much longer than calyx, infundibuliform to campanulate, with 5 wide,more or less incised lobes alternating with 5 linear segments (laciniae); throat naked, or with scales which alternate with the stamens. Capsule with a deciduous operculum and 5-10 teeth. Seeds small.
\par 

